        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1776114107
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13077#discussion_r3075615985\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This feels slightly brittle to me in that it's essentially re-serializing (un-parsing) (parts of) the command line for a subprocess: we may miss new options we add that we'd want to pass to the subprocess. I wonder if it would make sense to have a <code>.to_cmdline()</code> / <code>.serialize()</code> / ... method on the <code>RunCommand</code>?<br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 585281477,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1776114108
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13077#discussion_r3075793912\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Rather than manually baking in the invocation of Capstone here, could we reuse the innards of <code>wasmtime objdump</code> to get the disassembly? That keeps our logic and deps for disassembly to one place overall.</p>\n</blockquote>",
